<tal:block tal:define="hasRoleHelpDeskAdministrator here/isHelpDeskAdministrator; newissue python:request.get('newissue', '')">

	<div tal:condition="newissue">
		<p class="alert" i18n:translate="">
			Your submission has been received. If you entered a valid email you will
			be notified about any changes. If you marked your issue as confidential
			it will not appear in the listing unless released by an administrator.
		</p>
		<div style="padding-left: 2em;" tal:define="issue python:here.getIssuesObject(newissue)">
			<p>
				<span i18n:translate="" tal:omit-tag="">Last modified:</span>
				<span tal:replace="python:issue.FormatDate(issue.date_modify)" />,
				<span i18n:translate="" tal:omit-tag="">Opened:</span>
				<span tal:replace="python:issue.FormatDate(issue.date_open)" />,
				<span i18n:translate="" tal:omit-tag="">Ticket Number:</span>
				<span tal:replace="issue/id" />
			</p>

			<table style="text-align:left;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
				<colgroup>
					<col valign="top" />
				</colgroup>
				<tr>
					<th nowrap="nowrap" width="15%" i18n:translate="">Subject/Title</th>
					<td align="left"><span style="font-weight:bold" tal:content="issue/subject" /></td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<th nowrap="nowrap" valign="top" i18n:translate="">Description</th>
					<td class="celltextarea" align="left" tal:content="structure python:issue.EncodeTextareaContent(issue.description)" />
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td nowrap="nowrap" colspan="2" align="left">
						<span i18n:translate="" tal:omit-tag="">Status:</span>
						<span tal:replace="python:issue.getIssueStatusTitle(issue.status)" />,
						<span i18n:translate="" tal:omit-tag="">Priority:</span>
						<span tal:replace="python:issue.getIssuePriorityTitle(issue.priority)" />,
						<span i18n:translate="" tal:omit-tag="">Category:</span>
						<span tal:replace="python:issue.getIssueCategoryTitle(issue.category)" />
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<th nowrap="nowrap" i18n:translate="">Assigned to</th>
					<td align="left" tal:content="python:issue.getUserName(issue.consultant)" />
				</tr>
				<tr tal:condition="hasRoleHelpDeskAdministrator">
					<th nowrap="nowrap" i18n:translate="">Security</th>
					<td align="left" tal:content="issue/security" />
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td align="center" colspan="2"><strong i18n:translate="">User information</strong></td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<th nowrap="nowrap" i18n:translate="">Name</th>
					<td align="left" tal:content="issue/user_name" />
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<th nowrap="nowrap" i18n:translate="">Email</th>
					<td align="left" tal:content="issue/user_email" />
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<th nowrap="nowrap" i18n:translate="">Phone</th>
					<td align="left" tal:content="issue/user_phone" />
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<th nowrap="nowrap" i18n:translate="">Link</th>
					<td align="left"><a class="urllink" tal:condition="python:issue.link!=''" tal:attributes="href issue/link" target="_blank" tal:content="issue/link" /></td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<th nowrap="nowrap" i18n:translate="">Attachment</th>
					<td align="left" tal:define="res issue/getAttachmentForIssue; attobj python:res[0]; attFileName python:res[1]">
						<tal:block tal:condition="attobj">
							<a tal:attributes="href attobj/absolute_url" target="_blank" tal:content="attFileName" />
						</tal:block>
					</td>
				</tr>
			</table>
		</div>
	</div>

<tal:block condition="not:newissue">
	<p i18n:translate="">
		The HelpDesk Agent allows administrators of this portal to successfully
		track and respond to ticket HelpDesk issues. Documentation of relevant
		cases is kept into archives and it is easily accessible by performing
		searches using various filters: <em>List Issues</em>.
	</p>
	<h2 i18n:translate="">Usage</h2>
	<ul>
		<li i18n:translate="">
			insert your problem (issue) using one of the available forms -
			<strong>Post issue</strong> and <strong>Post quick issue</strong>.
			Use <em>quick issue</em> if you just want to notify the Issue 
			Administrator about a problem and you don't need follow-ups to it;
			in this case you will not be asked to insert your personal details.
			Otherwise, use the <em>Post issue</em> form<br /><br />
		</li>
		<li i18n:translate="">
			you will receive a confirmation e-mail when adding an issue and one
			for every modification brought to it (assignation of a person to handle
			the issue, comments added, etc.). Comments can be added by the person
			assigned to handle your request or by a regular end user of the portal
			<br /><br />
		</li>
		<li i18n:translate="">
			a ticket number will be automatically generated at addition time and
			you will be provided with the URL of the issue for later consultation
			<br /><br />
		</li>
		<li i18n:translate="">
			consult the evolution of the issues submitted by accessing the Issue
			tracker URL and listing issues<br /><br />
		</li>
		<li i18n:translate="">
			you are also able to consult and filter public issues and to add
			comments to them
		</li>
	</ul>
	<tal:block tal:condition="python:hasRoleHelpDeskAdministrator or here.isHelpDeskConsultant()">
	<h2 i18n:translate="">Issue management</h2>
	<ul>
		<li i18n:translate="">
			when new issues are posted, the Administrators receive e-mails with
			the URL and are in title to review the submission and edit it: by
			changing the <strong>Security</strong> from <em>private</em> to
			<em>public</em> the item will be visible for everyone; also, a Resolver
			can be assigned from the existing list to handle the issue. From that
			moment on, the Resolver will be also notified by e-mail about the changes
			in the item<br /><br />
		</li>
		<li i18n:translate="">
			Issue Administrators and Resolvers are able to filter and browse the
			entire archive of issues (public or not) and to add comments to any of
			them<br /><br />
		</li>
		<li i18n:translate="">
			Issue Resolvers are only able to edit and see the history of the issues
			that have been assigned to them, while the Administrators have full rights
			on all issues - edit, make public, view history, delete<br /><br />
		</li>
		<li i18n:translate="">
			Issue Administrators can consult the <em>Reports</em> that display statistics
			regarding the existing issues and resolvers that handle them<br /><br />
		</li>
	</ul>
	</tal:block>
</tal:block>
</tal:block>
